  "doc_id": "4607",
  "text": "Smaller femoral component size has previously been implicated as the risk factor accounting for the higher failure rate seen among women undergoing HRA [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . None of these studies have included diagnosis in their multivariable analysis. Our data is in agreement with these studies-we find that small component size is a more important risk factor than female gender; however, when the additional variable of diagnosis (OA or dysplasia) was added into the multivariable analysis model, femoral component size became an insignificant risk factor (P= 0.09). Component size was found to be significantly smaller in dysplasia than in OA (P<0.001).",
